Step 2: Create Your First Plan - "Project Setup"
Plan Name: "Project Setup & Configuration"
Plan Description:

Set up the foundation for the metal/woodworking landing page:
- Configure Tailwind with custom colors
- Set up layout with metadata
- Create reusable utility functions
- Establish dark mode defaults


Task 1: Update Tailwind Configuration

Update tailwind.config.ts to include our custom color palette:
- bronze: '#cd7f32', '#b87333'
- steel: '#71797E', '#52595D'  
- darkBg: '#0a0a0a', '#1a1a1a'
- accent: '#FFA500'

Add custom font families and extend theme with these colors.
Make sure to preserve existing Tailwind config.

Task 2: Configure Global Styles

Update app/globals.css:
- Set dark background (#0a0a0a) as default
- White text color
- Smooth scrolling behavior
- Custom scrollbar styling (dark theme)
- Remove any default blue/purple colors from shadcn

Task 3: Create Root Layout

Update app/layout.tsx:
- Add comprehensive metadata (title, description, og tags)
- Set up Inter font (or suggest modern industrial font)
- Include viewport settings for mobile
- Dark theme by default
- Basic structure with <html>, <body>


Task 4: Create Utility Functions

Create lib/utils.ts if it doesn't exist:
- Export 'cn' function for className merging
- Add any helper functions we'll need (formatDate, etc.)
